en_2706279_0	Colombo (News 1st): Twenty-four Sri Lankan fishermen and 4 fishing vessels have been apprehended by security officials patrolling the Maldives maritime boundary.
en_2706279_1	Director Operations of the Department of Fisheries Kalyani Hewapathirana said that the fishermen had departed from the Chilaw Fisheries Harbor in order to carry out their fishing activities.
en_2706279_2	She said investigations were underway to determine how a person under the age of 18 was among the arrested fishermen.
en_2706279_3	She added that the Maldivian government has been contacted in order to secure the release of the fishermen.
